5 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Direction to department of public health and human services. (1)
6 The legislature directs the department of public health and human services to apply to the centers for medicare
7 and medicaid services for a any necessary waiver and state plan amendment no later than January 1, 2028
8 2026, to make assisted living facility services currently covered under the big sky waiver a service covered
9 under the community first choice option available under the medicaid program to allow for medicaid-covered
10 assisted living services to be removed from the big sky waiver program and to be covered by the community
11 first choice option program.
12 (2) It is the intent of the legislature that the department transfer funding for assisted living services
13 from the big sky waiver program to the community first choice option program as individuals are moved from
14 the big sky waiver program, and its waitlist, to the community first choice option program. The amount
15 transferred will be the actual cost of serving the individuals receiving assisted living services under the
16 community first choice option program.
17 (3) Savings generated from the transfer of individuals to a lower-cost option will remain in the big
18 sky waiver program to be used to serve individuals waiting for home and community-based services remaining
19 in the waiver.
20
21 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Reporting requirements -- big sky waiver and community first
22 choice programs. (1) Each quarter of the 2029 2027 biennium, the department of public health and human
23 services shall report the following information for the preceding quarter to the health and human services
24 interim budget committee provided for in 5-12-501:
25 (a) the average number of people served each month through the big sky waiver and the
26 community first choice option administered by the division overseeing long-term care services;
27 (b) the average number of people on the waiting list for the big sky waiver each month;
